Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with video blending algorithms and evaluates their performance on a video benchmark. This is a core area of computer vision research. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper discusses various blending algorithms and evaluates their visual quality both objectively and subjectively. This is a key area of graphics research. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video blending, which is a key problem in multimedia applications such as virtual reality. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses the time and memory needed by the algorithms, which is relevant to robotics applications where real-time performance is critical. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper evaluates the performance of the algorithms on both CPU and GPU implementations, which is relevant to distributed and parallel computing research.
